{
  "info": {
    "name": "SkyBook Backend",
    "description": "Manual/demo requests for the SkyBook microservices.\n\nREAD FIRST — two things changed under this collection:\n1. EVERYTHING GOES THROUGH THE GATEWAY (http://localhost:8080). The per-service ports (8082/8083/8084/8086) are no longer published to the host at all — the security branch made every internal service, Postgres and Kafka expose:-only. The *_url variables all point at the gateway now.\n2. EVERY REQUEST NEEDS A TOKEN. Run Auth > Login first; it saves {{token}}, which the collection sends as a bearer token on every request. Without it you get 401.\n\nSome requests are ADMIN-only and will 403 for an ordinary account: creating flights/aircraft/inventory, listing all bookings, the refund ledger, and the gate operations (open window, board, assign gate, manifests). ADMIN cannot be granted through any API — auth-service promotes the address in SKYBOOK_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAIL once, at startup.\n\nFlow: Login -> pick a flight (Flights) -> create a booking (Bookings) -> pay (Payments) -> check in and board (Check-in & Boarding). Create Booking auto-saves {{bookingId}} and {{pnr}}; inventory requests auto-save {{aircraftId}}; check-in requests auto-save {{checkInId}}. The payment is auto-created by a Kafka consumer, so it appears a moment after the booking. Simulated gateway: amounts ending .13 decline authorization, .31 fail capture.\n\nThis collection is a DEMO artifact, not the certification suite — the executable source of truth is backend/e2e-tests (see E2E_CERTIFICATION_MODULE.md).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "auth_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "flight_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "booking_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "inventory_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "checkin_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "checkInId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "flightId",
      "value": "10"
    },
    {
      "key": "bookingId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "pnr",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "aircraftId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "payment_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    },
    {
      "key": "paymentId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "paymentReference",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Flights",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List all flights",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{flight_url}}/api/flights"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get flight by id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{flight_url}}/api/flights/{{flightId}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create flight",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{flight_url}}/api/flights",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightNumber\": \"SB101\",\n  \"airlineCode\": \"SB\",\n  \"originAirportCode\": \"HYD\",\n  \"destinationAirportCode\": \"LHR\",\n  \"departureTime\": \"2026-08-15T09:30:00\",\n  \"arrivalTime\": \"2026-08-15T19:45:00\"\n}"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Bookings",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create booking",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('bookingId', b.id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('pnr', b.bookingReference);",
                  "pm.test('201 created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('has PNR', () => pm.expect(b.bookingReference).to.be.a('string'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{booking_url}}/api/bookings",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"customerId\": 1,\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"passengers\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Mr\",\n      \"firstName\": \"Praveen\",\n      \"lastName\": \"Somireddy\",\n      \"dob\": \"1990-01-15\",\n      \"gender\": \"M\",\n      \"nationality\": \"IND\",\n      \"passportNumber\": \"N1234567\",\n      \"passportExpiry\": \"2030-06-30\",\n      \"email\": \"praveen.somireddy@gmail.com\",\n      \"travelClass\": \"ECONOMY\",\n      \"fareType\": \"FLEXI\",\n      \"seatNumber\": \"14A\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"contact\": {\n    \"contactName\": \"Praveen Somireddy\",\n    \"contactEmail\": \"praveen.somireddy@gmail.com\",\n    \"contactPhone\": \"+44 7700 900123\"\n  },\n  \"remarks\": \"postman collection booking\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Confirm booking (simulated payment)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{booking_url}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}/confirm"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get booking by PNR",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{booking_url}}/api/bookings/reference/{{pnr}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel booking",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{booking_url}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}/cancel",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reason\": \"cancelled via postman\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get all bookings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{booking_url}}/api/bookings"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Inventory & Reservations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Create aircraft",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('aircraftId', pm.response.json().id);",
                  "pm.test('201 created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/aircraft",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"registrationNumber\": \"VT-SKB\",\n  \"manufacturer\": \"Airbus\",\n  \"model\": \"A320neo\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Create seat map",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/aircraft/{{aircraftId}}/seat-map",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"seats\": [\n    { \"seatNumber\": \"1A\", \"rowNumber\": 1, \"seatType\": \"BUSINESS\", \"position\": \"WINDOW\" },\n    { \"seatNumber\": \"1C\", \"rowNumber\": 1, \"seatType\": \"BUSINESS\", \"position\": \"AISLE\" },\n    { \"seatNumber\": \"12A\", \"rowNumber\": 12, \"seatType\": \"ECONOMY\", \"position\": \"WINDOW\", \"exitRow\": true },\n    { \"seatNumber\": \"12B\", \"rowNumber\": 12, \"seatType\": \"ECONOMY\", \"position\": \"MIDDLE\" },\n    { \"seatNumber\": \"12C\", \"rowNumber\": 12, \"seatType\": \"ECONOMY\", \"position\": \"AISLE\" }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Get seat map",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/aircraft/{{aircraftId}}/seat-map"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Create flight inventory",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"aircraftId\": {{aircraftId}}\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Hold seat",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory/hold",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"seatNumber\": \"12A\",\n  \"bookingId\": {{bookingId}}\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Reserve seat (confirms the hold)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/reservations",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"seatNumber\": \"12A\",\n  \"bookingId\": {{bookingId}}\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7. Inventory counts for flight",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory/flight/{{flightId}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "8. Inventory history for flight",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory/flight/{{flightId}}/history"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "9. Cancel reservation",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/reservations/cancel",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"seatNumber\": \"12A\",\n  \"bookingId\": {{bookingId}},\n  \"reason\": \"postman test\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Release hold (alternative to reserve)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory/release",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"flightId\": {{flightId}},\n  \"seatNumber\": \"12A\",\n  \"bookingId\": {{bookingId}},\n  \"reason\": \"released via postman\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search inventories",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/inventory/search",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"OPEN\",\n  \"minAvailableSeats\": 1\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reservations by booking",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{inventory_url}}/api/reservations/booking/{{bookingId}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{auth_url}}/api/auth/register",
            "description": "Registration takes fullName (not firstName/lastName) and enforces a password policy: 12+ chars with upper, lower, digit and a symbol.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Praveen Somireddy\",\n  \"email\": \"praveen.somireddy@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"ChangeMe123!\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// The login response is the raw JWT (not JSON), so save it verbatim.",
                  "// Every other request in this collection inherits it as a bearer token.",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', pm.response.text().trim());",
                  "    console.log('token saved');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('login failed: ' + pm.response.code + ' ' + pm.response.text());",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{auth_url}}/api/auth/login",
            "description": "Run this FIRST. Saves {{token}}; without it every other request returns 401.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"praveen.somireddy@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"ChangeMe123!\"\n}"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Payments",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Get payment for booking (auto-created by consumer)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/booking/{{bookingId}}"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const p = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.json().paymentReference) pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentReference', pm.response.json().paymentReference);",
                  "if (p.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentId', p.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "1b. Create payment manually (Idempotency-Key)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"bookingId\": {{bookingId}},\n  \"bookingReference\": \"{{pnr}}\",\n  \"amount\": 100.00,\n  \"currency\": \"USD\",\n  \"fareLines\": [\n    { \"fareType\": \"FLEXI\", \"amount\": 100.00 }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Idempotency-Key",
                "value": "postman-{{bookingId}}"
              }
            ]
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const p = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.json().paymentReference) pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentReference', pm.response.json().paymentReference);",
                  "if (p.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentId', p.id);",
                  "pm.test('201 created or 200 replay', () => pm.expect([200,201]).to.include(pm.response.code));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Authorize",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/authorize"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Capture (issues invoice, publishes PAYMENT_SUCCEEDED)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/capture"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Get invoice",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/invoices/{{paymentId}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Refund (fare-type rules)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/refund",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reason\": \"postman refund test\"\n}"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Payment history (audit trail)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/history"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel (before capture)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/cancel"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get by reference",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments/reference/{{paymentReference}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List refunds",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/refunds"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "DECLINE demo: create with amount ending .13",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{payment_url}}/api/payments",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"bookingId\": 999913,\n  \"bookingReference\": \"SBDECL\",\n  \"amount\": 50.13,\n  \"currency\": \"USD\"\n}"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ]
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('paymentId', pm.response.json().id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Check-in & Boarding",
      "description": "Runs after a booking is CONFIRMED (i.e. after Payments capture). checkin-service creates the records itself by consuming the confirmed-booking event, so they appear a moment later - there is nothing to POST. Check-in and the boarding pass are passenger self-service; opening the window, assigning a gate and boarding are ADMIN (gate) operations and will 403 for an ordinary account.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Check-ins for my booking (auto-created by consumer)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const list = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (Array.isArray(list) && list.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('checkInId', list[0].id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('none yet - the booking must be CONFIRMED first, and the event takes a moment');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/checkins/booking/{{bookingId}}",
            "description": "Saves {{checkInId}}. Empty means the booking is not CONFIRMED yet."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Check in (passenger self-service)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/checkins/{{checkInId}}/checkin",
            "description": "Owner-only. 409 'does not open until ...' means the check-in window has not opened - it opens 24h before departure."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. My boarding pass",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/boarding-passes/checkin/{{checkInId}}",
            "description": "Owner-only. The 'token' field is the signature that makes the pass forgery-resistant."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Board the passenger (ADMIN / gate)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/checkins/{{checkInId}}/board",
            "description": "ADMIN only - a passenger cannot board themselves. Boarding opens 45 minutes before departure."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Baggage for a check-in",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/baggage/checkin/{{checkInId}}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Flight manifest (ADMIN)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{checkin_url}}/api/manifests/{{flightId}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}